# petrify

Petrify works by building up displacements.

The base displacement is the 2 Worley (Cellular) displacements which provide the classic "faceted" base rock shape.  Plug fields into the compound for detail displacement.
The two "main" displacements are written to a property (*cellular*) and is read with a ***property_proxy_field*** to combine wiht the details.

# Orthonormalize a matrix by the Gram-Schmidt process.
# The columns of the result matrix will be orthogonal and have unit length.
def orthonormalizeMatrix(A):
    column0 = A[:,0]
    # Normalize column 0
    column0 = column0 / np.linalg.norm(column0)
    A[:,0] = column0
    column1 = A[:,1]
    # Project column 1 onto column 0 and subtract to get an orthogonal vector
    column1 = column1 - np.dot(column0, column1) * column0
    # Normalize column 1
    column1 = column1 / np.linalg.norm(column1)
    A[:,1] = column1
    # Generate third column as cross product of column 0 and column 1
    A[:,2] = np.cross(column0, column1)
